---
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
import TermsLayout from '@/layouts/TermsLayout.astro';

const title = 'Terms and Conditions - LearnCode.live';
const description = "Terms and conditions governing the use of LearnCode.live website and services.";
---
<TermsLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <SEO title={title} description={description} />

  <div>
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-heading-1 text-ink dark:text-on-dark mb-2">Terms and Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone">Last updated: November 10, 2025</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-sm text-charcoal dark:text-on-dark-muted leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-heading-3 text-ink dark:text-on-dark mb-3">Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>Welcome to <strong>Learn Code Live</strong> (<a href="https://www.learncode.live" class="text-brand-green-deep dark:text-brand-green hover:underline">https://www.learncode.live</a>). These Terms and Conditions ("Terms") govern your use of our website and services. By accessing or using our website, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree with any part of these Terms, you must not use our website.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-heading-3 text-ink dark:text-on-dark mb-3">Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All content published on LearnCode.live, including but not limited to text, graphics, logos, images, code examples, tutorials, and software, is the property of LearnCode.live or its content creators and is protected by applicable intellectual property laws.</p>
        <p class="mt-2">You may access and use the content for personal, non-commercial educational purposes only. You may not reproduce, distribute, modify, create derivative works of, publicly display, or commercially exploit any content without prior written permission from LearnCode.live.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-heading-3 text-ink dark:text-on-dark mb-3">User Contributions</h2>
        <p>Users may have the opportunity to submit comments, suggestions, or other content ("Contributions"). By submitting Contributions, you grant LearnCode.live a non-exclusive, royalty-free, perpetual, and worldwide license to use, reproduce, modify, and display such Contributions in connection with the website.</p>
        <p class="mt-2">You represent and warrant that your Contributions are original, do not infringe on third-party rights, and are not unlawful or misleading. LearnCode.live reserves the right to remove any Contributions at its sole discretion.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-heading-3 text-ink dark:text-on-dark mb-3">Affiliate Links & Advertising</h2>
        <p>LearnCode.live may display third-party advertisements and affiliate links. When you click on an affiliate link and make a purchase, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you. We only promote products and services that we believe will provide value to our learners.</p>
        <p class="mt-2">We use Google AdSense to serve advertisements. Google and its partners may use cookies to serve ads based on your visits to our site and other websites. You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting Google's Ads Settings.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-heading-3 text-ink dark:text-on-dark mb-3">Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>LearnCode.live provides educational content on an "as is" and "as available" basis. We make no warranties, expressed or implied, regarding the accuracy, completeness, or reliability of the content. In no event shall LearnCode.live be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the website.</p>
        <p class="mt-2">The code examples and tutorials provided are for educational purposes. We are not responsible for any damages or losses resulting from the application of information obtained from this website.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-heading-3 text-ink dark:text-on-dark mb-3">Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Any disputes arising under these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in India.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-heading-3 text-ink dark:text-on-dark mb-3">Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>LearnCode.live reserves the right to modify these Terms at any time. Changes will be effective immediately upon posting on this page. We encourage users to review these Terms periodically. Your continued use of the website after any modifications indicates your acceptance of the updated Terms.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-heading-3 text-ink dark:text-on-dark mb-3">Contact Information</h2>
        <p>For any questions or concerns regarding these Terms, please contact us at:</p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Email: <a href="mailto:contact@learncode.live" class="text-brand-green-deep dark:text-brand-green hover:underline">contact@learncode.live</a><br />
          Website: <a href="https://www.learncode.live" class="text-brand-green-deep dark:text-brand-green hover:underline">https://www.learncode.live</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
